I don't like him
'cause he's lazy.

13:58.570 --> 14:00.458
And he's never applied himself
to anything.

14:00.500 --> 14:01.432
What do you mean?

14:01.470 --> 14:02.494
As soon as he was able,

14:02.540 --> 14:04.201
he cashed in his trust fund.

14:04.240 --> 14:05.559
He opened several restaurants
around London.

14:05.610 --> 14:08.306
Okay, so he's a
restauranteur...

14:08.340 --> 14:11.275
No, he's an indolent man-child,
and if I'd had my druthers,

14:11.310 --> 14:12.504
you would never have
crossed paths with him.

14:12.550 --> 14:15.041
Well, we're here now...
Tea?

14:15.080 --> 14:17.344
Help yourself.

14:18.690 --> 14:20.009
What have you done
with my things?

14:20.060 --> 14:21.652
Charity shops.

14:21.690 --> 14:23.180
You're joking.

14:23.230 --> 14:24.481
I reached out
to you several tImes

14:24.530 --> 14:25.485
in New York
to make arrangements.

14:25.530 --> 14:26.519
You never got back to me.

14:26.560 --> 14:28.448
I was in rehab.

14:28.500 --> 14:29.967
They don't have phones in rehab?

14:30.000 --> 14:32.525
See what I mean? Lazy.

14:32.570 --> 14:35.391
Could have had my things
properly stored, but didn't.

14:35.440 --> 14:36.907
Must I confess,

14:36.940 --> 14:38.430
I don't enjoy being
ambushed in my own home.

14:38.470 --> 14:40.131
It's a pleasure
to meet you, Joan.

14:40.180 --> 14:41.636
My father's mentioned you
several times.

14:41.680 --> 14:42.977
May I call you Joan?

14:43.010 --> 14:45.069
Yes, of course.

14:45.110 --> 14:46.577
It's funny that Sherlock's
never mentioned me to you.

14:46.610 --> 14:47.542
I wonder why that might be?

14:49.550 --> 14:51.040
Th-This again? Seriously?

14:51.090 --> 14:53.183
Maybe it's because
the last time I saw him

14:53.220 --> 14:55.586
he was face-deep in my fianc.

14:55.620 --> 14:57.087
What?

14:57.130 --> 14:58.552
It was five years ago, right?

14:58.590 --> 15:00.455
I had deduced that she was
far less interested in him

15:00.500 --> 15:02.092
than in the family fortune.

15:02.130 --> 15:04.269
I tried to warn him.
He wouldn't listen.

15:04.300 --> 15:06.325
So I set about proving
my hypothesis.

15:06.370 --> 15:07.928
Seven times, if memory serves.

15:07.970 --> 15:09.562
Once in a pod
on the London Eye.

15:10.670 --> 15:12.228
I did you a favor.

15:12.270 --> 15:15.478
You did what you wanted,
Sherlock.

15:15.510 --> 15:18.502
Just like you always do.

15:20.220 --> 15:23.439
I'm jet-lagged, Sherlock.

15:23.490 --> 15:26.709
So if we're not gonna stay here,
we need to find a hotel.

15:26.750 --> 15:28.149
MYCROFI':
Nonsense.

15:28.190 --> 15:31.250
Sherlock and I may have
our differences,

15:31.290 --> 15:32.587
but we're still family.

15:32.630 --> 15:36.020
You can both stay
in the guest rooms.

15:39.500 --> 15:41.730
(whispering): We've been up
for over 20 hours.

15:41.770 --> 15:43.658
It's nice here.

15:43.710 --> 15:45.359
Fine, fine.

15:45.410 --> 15:47.332
Only because time is
of the essence.

15:47.380 --> 15:49.302
Good.

15:49.340 --> 15:51.205
I'll fetch you
some fresh towels.

15:51.250 --> 15:53.639
Thank you so much.

15:53.680 --> 15:55.648
Right.
Where are you going?

15:55.680 --> 15:57.682
I've devised a theory
as to how to find Lestrade.

15:57.720 --> 15:59.210
I'd like to test it.

15:59.250 --> 16:01.684
You stay here. Rest.

16:23.780 --> 16:26.271
This is your idea
of lamming it, is it?

16:29.150 --> 16:31.482
A few pints in the heart
of Greenwich?

16:35.690 --> 16:37.624
So the...

16:37.660 --> 16:41.528
prodigal detective returns.

16:46.630 --> 16:48.791
And how-how-how'd
you find me?

16:48.840 --> 16:51.308
Once I learned
you hadn't withdrawn any cash,

16:51.340 --> 16:53.399
I had a good notion
what you were up to.

16:53.440 --> 16:55.579
You and I looked
into the matter

16:55.610 --> 16:57.498
of the Norwood Builder
together, didn't we?

16:57.550 --> 16:59.302
And during the course
of that investigation,

16:59.350 --> 17:01.511
I revealed to you
that I kept five hidden caches

17:01.550 --> 17:03.586
around the city.

17:03.620 --> 17:05.508
In case of emergencies.

17:05.550 --> 17:07.654
Cash, various passports,
other sundries,

17:07.690 --> 17:10.523
stood to reason you'd make use
of those in your hour of need.

17:10.560 --> 17:13.620
Four of the five
have been cleaned out.

17:13.660 --> 17:16.254
The fifth is in a hollowed-out
sculpture on the grounds

17:16.300 --> 17:18.188
of the library
across the street,

17:18.230 --> 17:19.492
and will be difficult to access

17:19.530 --> 17:21.259
until the security guard
goes off-duty.

17:21.300 --> 17:24.565
Actually, you know,
I'm-I'm-I'm quite pleased

17:24.610 --> 17:26.703
you're here really.

17:26.740 --> 17:28.071
I think you'd
be most impressed

17:28.110 --> 17:29.737
with all the work
that I've done.

17:29.780 --> 17:32.704
I am not here to consult
on the case of Lawrence Pendry.

17:32.750 --> 17:35.071
I am here to make quite certain

17:35.120 --> 17:37.111
that you emerge from hiding

17:37.150 --> 17:38.640
without harming yourself

17:38.690 --> 17:39.839
or anyone else.

17:39.890 --> 17:41.585
I felt I owed you that

17:41.620 --> 17:43.724
for all the years of work

17:43.760 --> 17:45.819
that we did together, so...

17:45.860 --> 17:48.693
Are you going to come
to Scotland Yard with me?

17:48.730 --> 17:51.494
Or shall I call them here?

17:56.240 --> 17:58.299
So, who you working with
in New York then?

17:58.340 --> 17:59.364
Captain Thomas Gregson.

17:59.410 --> 18:02.402
Good detective, good man.

18:02.440 --> 18:03.702
Not as sharp as you,
obviously.

18:03.750 --> 18:05.547
(chuckles)
Nice.

18:05.580 --> 18:07.616
What are you...
what are you doing?

18:07.650 --> 18:09.743
Well, the security man is off,

18:09.780 --> 18:12.613
so I thought I might go and get
myself a little bit of cash.

18:12.650 --> 18:13.617
Aw, don't... Just get...

18:13.660 --> 18:15.651
Get off me!

18:21.160 --> 18:22.195
You're being ridiculous.

18:22.230 --> 18:23.720
This is my case.

18:23.770 --> 18:26.864
I'm gonna be there
when Pendry is nicked.

18:26.900 --> 18:29.733
I mean, how many... how many
times did you follow some...

18:29.770 --> 18:32.238
some bonkers theory...

18:32.270 --> 18:33.874
and you'd find that
it was a complete

18:33.910 --> 18:35.468
and utter bloody
waste of time?

18:35.510 --> 18:37.808
What, 50, what,
a hundred times?

18:37.850 --> 18:39.306
See, I never got the chance
to follow my muse.

18:39.350 --> 18:40.669
(groans)

18:40.720 --> 18:44.315
I never even had the chance
to have an opInIon.

18:44.350 --> 18:46.648
Look, I acknowledge I was not
always the most attentive

18:46.690 --> 18:48.715
of colleagues.

18:48.760 --> 18:51.854
It's actually something
I'm taking steps to improve.

18:51.890 --> 18:53.699
And what good does that do me?

18:53.730 --> 18:55.698
Well... _
You can turn me In.

18:55.730 --> 18:57.664
You can do whatever
you want to do.

18:57.700 --> 18:59.668
Personally...

18:59.700 --> 19:01.861
what I would prefer, Sherlock,

19:01.900 --> 19:05.666
is that if you and I
could work together

19:05.710 --> 19:07.575
just one last time.

19:07.610 --> 19:09.805
(Mycroft speaking French)

19:10.810 --> 19:13.347
(speaking French)

19:14.720 --> 19:16.244
One of my suppliers

19:16.280 --> 19:17.747
from the restaurant--
I'll be a moment.

19:17.790 --> 19:20.816
(Mycroft speaking French)

19:24.460 --> 19:25.859
Sorry.

19:25.890 --> 19:28.529
Um, have you seen
Sherlock aanhere?

19:28.560 --> 19:30.323
He never came home last night.

19:30.370 --> 19:32.190
Are you sure?

19:32.230 --> 19:33.436
His bed was undisturbed.

19:33.470 --> 19:34.767
You live with him.

19:34.800 --> 19:36.438
Surely you know he'd
never sleep in it,

19:36.470 --> 19:37.960
then make it.

19:38.010 --> 19:40.934
Yeah, I guess I'll
try calling him.

19:40.980 --> 19:43.949
You must be learning
a great deal from him.

19:43.980 --> 19:45.709
Iam.

19:45.750 --> 19:47.638
How else would you
put up with him?

19:47.680 --> 19:50.615
Uh, I don't "put up" with him.

19:50.650 --> 19:53.312
We get along, basically.

19:53.360 --> 19:54.713
He's a friend.

19:54.760 --> 19:57.729
Sherlock doesn't have friends.

19:57.760 --> 19:59.887
Yesterday I would've told you
he doesn't have a brother.

19:59.930 --> 20:01.192
But he does.

20:03.800 --> 20:04.926
Does he?

20:04.970 --> 20:07.461
He's changed a lot.

20:07.500 --> 20:09.695
People often say that
about addicts, don't they?

20:09.740 --> 20:12.629
"He's changed, he's better now."

20:12.670 --> 20:15.833
Sherlock is addicted
to being himself.

20:15.880 --> 20:17.700
(phone chimes)

20:17.750 --> 20:19.775
MYCROFI':
Our boy?

20:19.810 --> 20:21.016
Yeah, he's fine.

20:21.050 --> 20:23.348
Uh, I'm gonna get dressed,

20:23.390 --> 20:25.779
and, uh, I'll go meet him.

20:26.850 --> 20:27.851
(sighs)

20:27.890 --> 20:29.949
(knife clunks on cutting board)

20:31.890 --> 20:32.652
WATSON :
Hey.

20:32.690 --> 20:35.750
Why are we
in an abandoned theater?

20:35.800 --> 20:37.791
These places come and go
as public subsidies

20:37.830 --> 20:39.491
wax and wane.

20:39.530 --> 20:41.839
A good place to hide,
if you are a fugitive.

20:43.410 --> 20:44.968
Fugitive?

20:45.010 --> 20:47.433
Joan Watson meet
Gareth Lestrade,

20:47.480 --> 20:49.436
late of Scotland Yard.

20:49.480 --> 20:51.903
Uh... pleasure.

20:51.950 --> 20:53.941
Hi.

20:54.950 --> 20:56.918
Yeah, hi.

20:56.950 --> 21:00.681
Okay, you found him and then you
came back to his lair with him.

21:00.720 --> 21:01.880
Is there any particular reason

21:01.920 --> 21:02.955
why you haven't called
the police?

21:02.990 --> 21:04.457
Yes. Milk.

21:06.090 --> 21:08.422
Lawrence Pendry is
lactose intolerant;

21:08.460 --> 21:09.893
his wife Mary,
a committed vegan;

21:09.930 --> 21:13.639
so why, then, is there a bottle
of milk in their fridge?

21:13.670 --> 21:15.365
Guests?
Perhaps.

21:15.400 --> 21:17.607
LESTRADE:
Uh, miss, no offense,

21:17.640 --> 21:19.437
but could you give him
a little bit of space, please?

21:19.470 --> 21:20.778
Because he's doing that thing.

21:20.810 --> 21:21.777
You know, when he's
on to something,

21:21.810 --> 21:22.834
he does that-that thing.

21:22.880 --> 21:25.542
Yes, I-I know that thing.

21:27.750 --> 21:29.547
You didn't tell me that one
of your brother's restaurants

21:29.580 --> 21:31.684
had two Michelin Stars.

21:31.720 --> 21:32.982
(scoffs)
I didn't tell you

21:33.020 --> 21:34.317
that my brother
was a corporal entity.

21:34.360 --> 21:35.952
You've been chatting

21:35.990 --> 21:38.925
with Mycroft?
Yes, he wants
to take me to dinner.

21:40.030 --> 21:41.019
What?

21:41.060 --> 21:42.459
He intends to bed you.

21:42.500 --> 21:44.024
(sighs)

21:44.070 --> 21:45.822
Retaliation for my misadventures
with his fianc.

21:45.870 --> 21:48.862
Misadventures is not
the word that I would use.

21:48.900 --> 21:50.936
You are attracted to Mycroft.

21:50.970 --> 21:53.006
Um, no, I'm not.

21:53.040 --> 21:54.473
Hm. Makes a certain
amount of sense.

21:54.510 --> 21:55.829
It's classic
transference.

21:55.880 --> 21:57.575
You wouldn't be
sleeping with him.

21:57.610 --> 21:59.976
Psychologically speaking,
you'd be sleeping with me.

22:00.010 --> 22:01.910
Oh, you surely
thought about it.

22:01.950 --> 22:03.588
You can't go
to bed with me.

22:03.620 --> 22:04.917
We're business partners

22:04.950 --> 22:06.611
and you're my former
sober companion.

22:06.650 --> 22:08.857
But you can sleep with
a cheap knockoff version of me,

22:08.890 --> 22:10.585
and that is Mycroft.

22:10.630 --> 22:11.983
(sighs)
I don't even know

22:12.030 --> 22:14.021
what I'm supposed
to be looking for in here.

22:14.060 --> 22:17.325
One of these ma... one of these
masks Is out of place.

22:21.940 --> 22:24.966
They look pretty well
lined up to me.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.932
Yes, well,
they are "pretty well lined up,"

22:26.970 --> 22:28.506
but they were...

22:30.180 --> 22:31.909
...perfectly lined up.

22:31.950 --> 22:33.941
Mary Pendry took this photograph
of herself

22:33.980 --> 22:37.416
and e-mailed it to a friend,
just hours before she died.

22:37.450 --> 22:38.883
In it, the third mask
from the left

22:38.920 --> 22:40.649
is perfectly in line
with its compatriots.

22:40.690 --> 22:44.421
But this one,
it's just a little bit lower.

22:44.460 --> 22:45.984
Did you notice this
at the scene?

22:46.030 --> 22:47.952
The murder weapon
could be hidden here.

22:48.000 --> 22:48.955
Eh, did I notice
the discrepancy?

22:49.000 --> 22:50.524
Hm.
No.

22:50.570 --> 22:51.821
But we're not
complete IdIots.

22:51.870 --> 22:52.962
We did check
behind the mask,

22:53.000 --> 22:54.433
and there was
no gun there.

22:54.470 --> 22:55.869
I need to examine this room.

22:55.900 --> 22:57.436
Well, this is
not our case.

22:57.470 --> 22:59.461
Pendry's not
gonna just let
us walk in there.

22:59.510 --> 23:00.909
Well, he will when I tell him
that I almost

23:00.940 --> 23:02.976
caught his enemy Lestrade,

23:03.010 --> 23:04.671
and I found a suicide note
that he was writing

23:04.710 --> 23:06.007
in which he indicates
his intention

23:06.050 --> 23:07.745
to murder Lawrence Pendry.

23:07.780 --> 23:09.975
But I haven't written
any SUIClde notes.

23:10.020 --> 23:12.443
Not yet you haven't.

23:12.490 --> 23:16.688
PENDRY: "I die knowing that
I brought justice to Mary.

23:16.720 --> 23:20.087
I die vindicated,
a true policeman."

23:20.130 --> 23:21.859
Do you actually think
he'll follow through?

23:21.900 --> 23:22.924
Difficult to say.

23:22.960 --> 23:24.461
You might want
to take different

23:24.500 --> 23:26.468
routes to your office.
Inform your security.

23:26.500 --> 23:28.934
I'm-_I'm sure that
the po|Ice WIll be happy
to send someone over.

23:28.970 --> 23:30.938
With all due respect,
I'm protecting myself

23:30.970 --> 23:32.631
from a member of the police.

23:32.670 --> 23:33.932
I'm hardly likely to invite
more of them

23:33.980 --> 23:35.732
into my home.

23:35.780 --> 23:37.873
Thank you for bringing this
to my attention.

23:37.910 --> 23:41.038
We'll take_
every precautIon.

23:41.080 --> 23:42.718
Was there something else?

23:42.750 --> 23:44.183
Well...

23:44.220 --> 23:46.040
Miss Watson first came
to my attentIon

23:46.090 --> 23:49.810
as America's foremost expert
on home security, so...

23:49.860 --> 23:52.055
perhaps she could take
a look around, hmm?

23:52.090 --> 23:54.729
See if everything's
up to snuff.

23:54.760 --> 23:56.819
I suppose so.

23:56.860 --> 23:58.418
Thank you.

23:59.670 --> 24:01.888
It's what I do.

24:01.940 --> 24:06.036
We've got motion detectors
at each end of the corridors,

24:06.070 --> 24:08.209
security nodes
on all the windows.

24:10.180 --> 24:13.206
Well, Miss Watson,
what do you think?

24:13.250 --> 24:15.138
It's secure.

24:15.180 --> 24:16.818
It's very secure.

24:16.850 --> 24:19.819
High praise indeed,
from the likes of her.

24:19.850 --> 24:22.978
Don't know what else
there Is to say.

24:23.020 --> 24:25.488
Again, shatterproof glass,

24:25.530 --> 24:27.179
security nodes on all
the windows.

24:27.230 --> 24:29.755
And what is the
floodlight situation
on the windows?

24:29.800 --> 24:31.028
Fully covered, of course.

24:31.070 --> 24:32.025
(nail clinking,
rattling onto floor)

24:32.070 --> 24:33.196
Motion-sensitive.

24:33.230 --> 24:34.993
We replace the bulbs
the minute they go out.

24:35.040 --> 24:38.066
Excuse me. _
What are you domg?

24:38.110 --> 24:39.702
I'm so sorry.
So sorry.

24:39.740 --> 24:45.007
Ijust, uh...
I love folk art.

24:45.050 --> 24:47.200
Thank you very much.

24:47.250 --> 24:49.514
We'll be in touch
when we have Lestrade.

24:49.550 --> 24:51.142
Yes.

24:55.220 --> 24:59.088
You had to tell him
I was the number one
home securIty expert?

24:59.130 --> 25:00.552
You couldn't have
told him

25:00.600 --> 25:01.919
I was number eight
or something?

25:01.960 --> 25:03.257
You acquitted
yourself admirably.

25:03.300 --> 25:05.120
Anyway, it was
time well spent.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.592
You found something?

25:06.630 --> 25:08.188
Lestrade was right.

25:08.240 --> 25:09.639
Lawrence Pendry
did kill his wife.

25:09.670 --> 25:11.968
I know exactly
how he did it.

25:16.180 --> 25:18.239
HOLMES: 13 months ago,
a neighbor heard the shot

25:18.280 --> 25:20.840
which took Mary Pendry's life
at exactly 6:33.

25:22.750 --> 25:24.581
I just want to know what you
found in that bastard's house.

25:24.620 --> 25:26.315
The primary reason
you were never able

25:26.350 --> 25:28.181
to build a case against Pendry

25:28.220 --> 25:30.688
was that you could not find
the murder weapon.

25:30.730 --> 25:34.894
I humbly submit that it was
in the kitchen the entire time.

25:34.930 --> 25:36.625
No, you see, that's bollocks,

25:36.660 --> 25:38.059
'cause we turned the whole house
upSIde down.

25:38.100 --> 25:39.920
There was absolutely no gun.

25:39.970 --> 25:43.736
That's because you made the
mistake of looking for a gun.

25:45.670 --> 25:47.308
This is the weapon
that I believe

25:47.340 --> 25:49.604
Pendry used
to kill his wife.

25:49.640 --> 25:51.779
A plastic gun.

25:51.810 --> 25:53.175
You're absolutely right.

25:53.210 --> 25:54.347
Yes, I did see one
of those, actually.

25:54.380 --> 25:55.847
It was in the cutlery drawer.

25:55.880 --> 25:57.711
Thought it was a toy,
so I left it alone.

25:57.750 --> 25:59.286
You think I'm daft?

25:59.320 --> 26:02.357
What, you think I wouldn't
recognize a plastic gun?

26:02.390 --> 26:04.779
We don't think
it looked like that

26:04.830 --> 26:08.596
by the time you got there;
we think it looked like this.

26:08.630 --> 26:10.257
HOLMES: I don't believe
that it was milk

26:10.300 --> 26:12.666
in that bottle;
I believe it was acetone.

26:12.700 --> 26:14.691
Acetone?

26:14.740 --> 26:17.095
He used acetone
to melt the gun.

26:17.140 --> 26:19.267
The crime, as I see it,

26:19.310 --> 26:21.972
Pendry shoots his wife
at 6:33.

26:22.010 --> 26:24.001
He the disassembles his weapon
and he drops the pieces

26:24.050 --> 26:26.678
into a bottle
he's filled with acetone.

26:26.710 --> 26:29.770
He then dials 999 at 6:36

26:29.820 --> 26:32.186
to report that his wife has
been murdered by an intruder.

26:32.220 --> 26:33.209
The acetone, meanwhile,
is dissolving

26:33.250 --> 26:34.979
the gun he used to murder her,

26:35.020 --> 26:37.318
leaving nothing but a milk-like
liquid in the bottle

26:37.360 --> 26:39.681
in his refrigerator.

26:39.730 --> 26:41.357
It's unbelievable.

26:41.400 --> 26:45.029
And all of this from
a photograph of a pint of milk?

26:45.070 --> 26:46.662
And a nail.

