it makes it possible
for anyone with the right specs

26:55.710 --> 26:57.871
to build one in the comfort
of their own home.

26:57.910 --> 27:00.674
They only need one piece
of metal to make it work:

27:00.720 --> 27:03.689
a nail to act as the firing pin.

27:03.720 --> 27:05.813
Now, Pendry couldn't very well
melt a nail, could he?

27:05.850 --> 27:07.659
So he hid it in plain sight.

27:07.690 --> 27:09.385
He used it to re-hang
one of the masks

27:09.420 --> 27:10.921
in the living room
before the police arrived.

27:10.960 --> 27:12.689
That's why it was hanging

27:12.730 --> 27:14.891
lower than the others--
He did the work in a hurry.

27:14.930 --> 27:17.398
When I examined that nail today,

27:17.430 --> 27:20.319
I noticed that the tip
was slightly charred.

27:20.370 --> 27:22.338
Carbon scoring

27:22.370 --> 27:24.634
from where
it struck the bullet.

27:26.270 --> 27:27.430
I was right.

27:27.470 --> 27:30.109
I always knew it, you see?
I always knew.

27:30.140 --> 27:32.347
Ijust didn't... I...

27:32.380 --> 27:35.110
I need to take
this case to Hopkins.

27:35.150 --> 27:37.277
And I don't care
if he... he bangs me up

27:37.320 --> 27:39.686
for what I did at the funeral.

27:39.720 --> 27:41.449
I just want to see
that bastard rot!

27:41.490 --> 27:44.687
All we have is a nail
with a blackened tip.

27:44.730 --> 27:46.755
Any number of reasons
that could have happened.

27:46.790 --> 27:49.725
The gunshot residue would have
worn off ages ago.

27:49.760 --> 27:52.797
We have no way to prove that
it was ever part of a weapon.

27:52.830 --> 27:56.095
If we are to undo him,

27:56.140 --> 27:59.268
we need to find out more
about how and where

27:59.310 --> 28:01.130
he made that gun.

28:03.340 --> 28:05.740
London, like New York,
is a beacon of freedom

28:05.780 --> 28:07.475
and a target
for terrorists.

28:07.510 --> 28:09.239
It is, as a consequence,

28:09.280 --> 28:12.010
one of the most observed
cities in the world.

28:12.050 --> 28:16.089
Its network of thousands
upon thousands of CCTV cameras

28:16.120 --> 28:17.951
track the movements
of its citizens,

28:17.990 --> 28:20.356
looking for anything
at all out of place.

28:20.390 --> 28:22.358
Yeah, I noticed.
They're kind of everywhere.

28:22.400 --> 28:24.265
Mm. Now I know for a fact

28:24.300 --> 28:25.927
that some of England's
network of watchmen

28:25.970 --> 28:27.426
verge on the competent.

28:27.470 --> 28:29.938
I would wager that,
like us, they're aware

28:29.970 --> 28:32.734
of the new and deadly
advances in 3-D printing.

28:32.770 --> 28:35.409
I would also wager
that the nation's gun-averse

28:35.440 --> 28:36.873
and ever-more-paranoid
security apparatus

28:36.910 --> 28:41.370
are tracking the sales
of 3-D printers.

28:41.420 --> 28:42.819
Would you mind?

28:42.850 --> 28:44.784
If they are,
it should be a simple matter

28:44.820 --> 28:46.117
of consulting
their database,

28:46.150 --> 28:48.311
see if we can
connect one to Pendry.

28:52.430 --> 28:54.250
since they became GPS—capable.

28:54.300 --> 28:56.450
He doesn't like the idea that
one could be used to track him.

28:56.500 --> 28:58.388
Now what?

28:58.430 --> 29:00.489
Now we wait.

29:11.850 --> 29:13.818
We've been here
for over four hours.

29:13.850 --> 29:16.774
Are you sure you're
just not using this as an excuse

29:16.820 --> 29:18.481
so I don't have dinner
with your brother?

29:18.520 --> 29:20.385
I've decided I don't have
a problem with it.

29:20.420 --> 29:21.512
What, dinner?

29:21.560 --> 29:23.016
The retaliatory sex.

29:23.060 --> 29:24.857
You're an adult.
You can do as you please.

29:24.890 --> 29:26.528
Might even be good for you;
clear your mind.

29:26.560 --> 29:28.050
You know what?
For the last time,

29:28.100 --> 29:30.523
no one is having sex
with anyone, okay?

29:30.560 --> 29:33.028
He wants to get to know me
because I am your partner.

29:33.070 --> 29:35.436
I want to get to know him
because he is your brother.

29:35.470 --> 29:37.233
You hope to learn secrets
from my childhood.

29:37.270 --> 29:38.806
Mycroft will be of little use.

29:38.840 --> 29:39.932
We went to separate
boarding schools.

29:39.970 --> 29:42.404
Oh! Hey, cheers!

29:42.440 --> 29:43.873
Congratulations, Watson.

29:43.910 --> 29:46.777
You just met Langdale Pike.

29:52.250 --> 29:54.559
WATSON: Wow, looks like the 3-D
printing business has been good.

29:54.590 --> 29:56.387
Mm.
I shall let you know

29:56.420 --> 29:57.580
if Lestrade
and I find anything.

29:57.620 --> 29:58.882
What... what,
you're ditching me?

29:58.930 --> 30:00.852
I'm conducting
an experiment.

30:00.900 --> 30:02.856
I'm curious to know
which of us is right
about my brother.

30:02.900 --> 30:03.889
My money's on me.

30:03.930 --> 30:05.591
Bon appetit.

30:05.630 --> 30:08.531
WATSON:
Hello?

30:08.570 --> 30:11.061
MYCROFT:
Joan!

30:11.110 --> 30:12.566
Right on time.

30:12.610 --> 30:14.874
I was, uh, digging around
in the cellar.

30:14.910 --> 30:16.878
Wasn't sure whether you liked
red or white,

30:16.910 --> 30:18.605
so I excavated a bottle of both.

30:18.650 --> 30:22.370
Um, is the restaurant
closed tonight?

30:22.420 --> 30:24.888
My prettiest eatery by far,
but the acoustics are rubbish.

30:24.920 --> 30:27.957
This way we'll have
a decent conversation.

30:29.320 --> 30:31.857
You know there's nothing
happening here, right?

30:33.960 --> 30:36.895
You thought this was
a romantic engagement?

30:36.930 --> 30:39.592
It's not?

30:39.630 --> 30:41.598
Please sit down.

30:47.270 --> 30:48.931
There's something
I wanted

30:48.980 --> 30:50.629
to discuss with you
in private.

30:50.680 --> 30:53.274
I thought it was
a conversation best lubricated

30:53.310 --> 30:55.141
with good food
and good wine.

30:58.520 --> 31:01.580
(clears throat)

31:01.620 --> 31:05.420
I, um...

31:05.460 --> 31:08.156
lied to Sherlock yesterday
when I told him

31:08.200 --> 31:09.394
I'd lost weight via exercise.

31:09.430 --> 31:10.897
The truth is...

31:10.930 --> 31:11.919
You were sick.

31:15.570 --> 31:18.061
I noticed the scars _
on your erst thIs mornIng.

31:18.110 --> 31:19.668
Graft-versus-host?

31:19.710 --> 31:23.942
You had a bone
marrow transplant

31:23.980 --> 31:26.676
some time in the last...
two years?

31:26.710 --> 31:28.644
If I didn't know you were
an ex-surgeon,

31:28.680 --> 31:31.217
I'd say you've been spending
too much time with my brother.

31:31.250 --> 31:32.512
(chuckles)

31:32.550 --> 31:33.687
That's actually
what I wanted

31:33.720 --> 31:36.917
to discuss with you
this evening;

31:36.960 --> 31:38.951
time with my brother.

31:41.400 --> 31:43.220
You're right, of course,
about everything.

31:43.260 --> 31:44.693
I was sick, very sick.

31:44.730 --> 31:46.288
When I wasn't vomiting,

31:46.330 --> 31:48.093
I found myself prone
to reflection.

31:48.140 --> 31:52.406
It dawned on me the one regret
I have in life was

31:52.440 --> 31:55.307
the state of my relationship
with Sherlock.

31:55.340 --> 31:58.047
I hadn't asked him
to see if he'd be a match.

31:58.080 --> 32:00.446
You see, I hadn't even told him
I was ill.

32:00.480 --> 32:04.985
And as my condition
improved, I decided

32:05.020 --> 32:06.681
I'd figure out an approach;

32:06.720 --> 32:08.517
some way to make things better.

32:08.560 --> 32:11.484
But then, of course, he showed
up on my doorstep yesterday,

32:11.530 --> 32:12.679
and Ijust...

32:12.730 --> 32:16.052
fell into old habits.

32:16.100 --> 32:20.662
You're obviously
Sherlock's friend.

32:20.700 --> 32:23.669
As I mentioned, Sherlock's never
had any friends.

32:23.700 --> 32:27.659
Many colleagues,
never a friend... until you.

32:27.710 --> 32:31.703
I want to know
how you did it.

32:31.750 --> 32:35.015
I want to know...

32:35.050 --> 32:38.941
how does one become
Sherlock Holmes' friend?

32:42.720 --> 32:46.349
HOLMES: Look, (clears throat)
I owe you an apology...

32:46.390 --> 32:49.951
for not protecting you
when we worked together.

32:53.200 --> 32:54.428
Protecting me from what?

32:54.470 --> 32:57.496
From the spotlight,
the attention.

32:57.540 --> 32:59.064
(chuckles)
Those were some

32:59.110 --> 33:01.408
of the best days
of my career.

33:01.440 --> 33:03.579
You know, my name
was in the paper,

33:03.610 --> 33:05.703
my face was on the telly.

33:05.750 --> 33:07.149
The whole thing,
it was, it was...

33:07.180 --> 33:08.670
It was intoxicating, hm?

33:08.720 --> 33:10.278
Yeah, well, I was gonna say
it was everything

33:10.320 --> 33:11.742
I dreamed about being
a policeman,

33:11.790 --> 33:14.111
but that as well, yeah.

33:14.160 --> 33:16.583
I'm glad we helped
so many people.

33:16.620 --> 33:17.587
Well, I helped them.

33:17.620 --> 33:18.621
You only said you did.

33:18.660 --> 33:19.752
Well, I...

33:19.790 --> 33:22.429
No...

33:22.460 --> 33:23.757
my carelessness had
a negative impact,

33:23.800 --> 33:25.620
and, um...

33:25.670 --> 33:30.596
I'd like to, uh,
I'd like to make amends.

33:30.640 --> 33:34.201
So, um... Ijust,
I-I-I wrote some...

33:34.240 --> 33:35.707
(clears throat)

33:35.740 --> 33:36.707
I wrote some things...

33:36.740 --> 33:38.105
Hello.

33:38.150 --> 33:40.277
...down.
It says here that...

33:40.310 --> 33:42.312
Pendry had this handyman,
this guy called Nick Ginn.

33:42.350 --> 33:43.544
and he was _
a small-tIme VIIIaIn,

33:43.580 --> 33:45.081
and we had him in
for questioning.

33:45.120 --> 33:46.712
But he had an alibi
the night of the murder.

33:46.750 --> 33:48.115
All right, now it says

33:48.160 --> 33:50.048
that he bought a 3D printer

33:50.090 --> 33:52.251
one week before
Mary Pendry died.

33:53.860 --> 33:57.227
Pendry paid him
to buy the printer.

33:57.260 --> 33:58.591
And then he built the gun.

33:59.530 --> 34:00.827
Hm.

34:00.870 --> 34:02.690
Now if Ginn still
has the printer,

34:02.740 --> 34:05.459
or if we can compel him
to confirm our hypothesis,

34:05.510 --> 34:07.637
We can prove...

34:07.670 --> 34:09.228
that I was right.

34:09.280 --> 34:10.304
(knocking on door)

34:11.480 --> 34:13.471
Open up, Nicky!

34:20.190 --> 34:21.452
I sorted it,
you know.

34:21.490 --> 34:23.378
Sorted what?

34:23.420 --> 34:26.287
A way you can make amends.

34:26.330 --> 34:29.094
Let me take the
credit for this one,

34:29.130 --> 34:31.462
and we'll be square.

34:31.500 --> 34:34.139
Come on, I deserve it.

34:36.200 --> 34:38.168
Pendry's mine.

34:58.890 --> 35:00.187
HOLMES:
Nicholas Ginn.

35:00.230 --> 35:01.629
I obviously riled Pendry

35:01.660 --> 35:03.355
when I examined
the charred nail today.

35:03.400 --> 35:05.288
He decided
to tie up loose ends

35:05.330 --> 35:07.764
by murdering his accomplice.

35:07.800 --> 35:09.836
He cleaned_the scene
qUIte metIculously.

35:09.870 --> 35:11.667
Yeah, I passed DCI
Hopkins on the way in.

35:11.710 --> 35:12.836
He didn't seem very happy.

35:12.870 --> 35:15.270
He knows I've been
helping Lestrade.

35:15.310 --> 35:16.777
He wants me to give up
his location,

35:16.810 --> 35:18.300
but I would prefer not to

35:18.350 --> 35:20.341
_ until his case
agaInst Pendry has been made.

35:20.380 --> 35:22.678
And yet...

35:22.720 --> 35:25.382
I don't suppose you found
a 3D printer in here?

35:25.420 --> 35:27.285
Pendry obviously
destroyed that ages ago.

35:27.320 --> 35:29.151
Why obviously?

35:29.190 --> 35:30.452
Ginn is six-foot-four.

35:30.490 --> 35:32.481
He has at least
two stone on Pendry.

35:32.530 --> 35:33.827
If he still had access
to the printer,

35:33.860 --> 35:35.225
don't you think
he would've built himself

35:35.260 --> 35:37.490
another gun to kill Ginn, hmm?

35:37.530 --> 35:39.669
It would've been
the safer way to go by far.

35:39.700 --> 35:42.635
There's just so little here
that makes sense.

35:42.670 --> 35:44.365
I know.

35:44.410 --> 35:46.799
He used one of the victim's
own knives to kill him.

35:46.840 --> 35:48.535
You think a planner like Pendry

35:48.580 --> 35:49.831
would've brought
a weapon of his own.

35:49.880 --> 35:53.543
Also the sta_b wound
was obVIously

35:53.580 --> 35:55.343
the result
of a left-handed blow.

35:55.380 --> 35:56.642
But Pendry is right-handed,

35:56.680 --> 35:58.887
so why would he use
his non-dominant hand

35:58.920 --> 36:01.184
to stab someone to death?

36:01.220 --> 36:02.858
You knew Pendry was
a righty, right?

36:02.890 --> 36:05.358
Yeah, of course.

36:07.290 --> 36:08.689
What are you doing?

36:25.980 --> 36:28.813
*

36:40.030 --> 36:41.918
Well, I was wrong, Watson.

36:41.960 --> 36:44.793
Pendry does still have
a printer.

36:44.830 --> 36:47.492
And he used it
to build another gun.

36:47.530 --> 36:48.531
(knocking on door)

36:50.400 --> 36:51.537
Good evening.

36:51.570 --> 36:52.639
I have a confession to make.

36:52.670 --> 36:53.705
Miss Watson is not, in fact,

36:53.740 --> 36:55.970
a home security specialist.

36:56.010 --> 36:57.807
Dan, pick up the phone
for God's sake.

36:57.840 --> 37:00.638
I've got police in my house
and I need my solicitor.

37:02.850 --> 37:04.317
If that's
what you're here for,

37:04.350 --> 37:05.908
then just take it and leave.

37:05.950 --> 37:08.282
This? No, no, you've changed
this since yesterday.

37:08.320 --> 37:11.778
Aanay, we're not here regarding
the murder of your wife Mary.

37:11.830 --> 37:13.889
We're here about the death
of Nicholas Ginn.

37:13.930 --> 37:15.750
VVho?
WATSON: Your
ex-handyman.

37:15.800 --> 37:17.392
The one who bought the
printer that made the gun

37:17.430 --> 37:18.863
you used to kill Mary.

37:18.900 --> 37:20.993
After I looked at that nail,
you panicked.

37:21.030 --> 37:22.566
You went to wherever
you're hIdIng the prInter,

37:22.600 --> 37:24.602
and you built yourself
another gun.

37:24.640 --> 37:25.732
You went to kill Ginn.

37:25.770 --> 37:26.907
But when you fired,

37:26.940 --> 37:28.373
the gun exploded in your hand.

37:28.410 --> 37:29.877
When you killed Mary,

37:29.910 --> 37:32.276
you used a special-order
.22-caliber round.

37:32.310 --> 37:33.948
Today, you were in a hurry.

37:33.980 --> 37:35.277
You used a .22 long.

37:35.320 --> 37:36.969
Mm. Higher velocity
bullet can cause

37:37.020 --> 37:38.885
the plastic pistol
to explode.

37:38.920 --> 37:40.740
Ginn lunged at you.

37:40.790 --> 37:42.758
You grabbed a knife
with your uninjured left hand

37:42.790 --> 37:43.814
The heavier man

37:43.860 --> 37:45.725
threw himself onto the blade.

37:45.760 --> 37:47.489
You did a decent job
of cleaning the scene.

37:47.530 --> 37:49.623
You found every piece
of the gun.

37:49.660 --> 37:52.766
Except for the pieces
that landed in Ginn's fruit.

37:52.800 --> 37:54.791
WATSON: Now, if you
fired the weapon,

37:54.840 --> 37:57.035
you'd have wounds on
your right forearm.

37:57.070 --> 37:58.662
We just need to
take a look.

37:58.710 --> 38:01.065
Mm. Which, as it happens,
is exactly

38:01.110 --> 38:03.431
what his warrant
empowers mm to do.

38:03.480 --> 38:06.040
(phone ringing)
HOLMES: It's going to be
your solicitor.

38:06.080 --> 38:08.947
You can just tell him
you're heading into custody.

38:10.920 --> 38:13.912
(siren warbling)

38:21.730 --> 38:23.994
Thank you.

38:24.030 --> 38:25.668
Well, lads,
you can take me to nick.

38:25.700 --> 38:27.725
Detective?

38:27.770 --> 38:29.692
I thank you not to take credit

38:29.740 --> 38:32.061
for any of my insights
into the case.

38:32.110 --> 38:35.079
Right, so your whole
making it up to me

38:35.110 --> 38:36.873
was just a complete
and utter lie.

38:36.910 --> 38:38.036
Was it?

38:38.080 --> 38:40.708
I will not enable you anymore.

38:40.750 --> 38:43.742
I am withdrawing
your drug of choice.

38:43.780 --> 38:45.680
Right.

38:45.720 --> 38:48.109
It's back to obscurity
for me then.

38:48.150 --> 38:49.811
Don't be a stranger.

38:56.100 --> 38:58.091
LESTRADE (on TV):
Of course, I stay current

38:58.130 --> 39:01.395
to the capabilities
of the 3D printers.

39:01.440 --> 39:04.364
I always knew
that Lawrence Pendry

39:04.410 --> 39:07.106
was, in fact, guilty and had
actually murdered his wife.

39:07.140 --> 39:10.371
I just needed to figure out
how and... and why.

39:10.410 --> 39:12.776
He called your bluff.

39:12.810 --> 39:16.610
He knows you'll never step
forward to take the credit.

39:16.650 --> 39:19.847
Curious.

39:19.890 --> 39:22.711
I never felt this particular
cocktail of emotions.

39:22.760 --> 39:25.627
Anger, exasperation...

39:25.660 --> 39:28.629
and a hint of...

39:28.660 --> 39:30.821
Worry?

39:30.860 --> 39:32.999
Yeah, well, welcome
to caring about an addict.

39:33.030 --> 39:35.032
(phone dings)

39:35.070 --> 39:36.697
WEATHERMAN: With seasonal
temperatures, we should reach

39:36.740 --> 39:38.560
our normal high
of about 82 degrees

39:38.610 --> 39:39.668
by this afternoon.

39:39.710 --> 39:41.735
Clear skies tonight...

39:49.750 --> 39:51.172
All right, Fatty,
let's make this quick.

39:51.220 --> 39:53.984
Watson and I have
a plane to catch.

39:54.020 --> 39:55.487
You said it was urgent.

39:55.520 --> 39:56.885
Take a seat, would you?

39:56.920 --> 39:59.150
Only take a moment.

40:04.470 --> 40:06.597
I lied to you the other day,

40:06.630 --> 40:09.565
when I said I'd given
all your stuff to charity.

40:09.600 --> 40:11.739
It's in storage.

40:11.770 --> 40:13.431
Over there, behind that door.

40:19.550 --> 40:21.677
I bet you expect me
to thank you, don't you?

40:21.720 --> 40:24.211
Well, you're lucky I didn't
turn it all in to the police.

40:24.250 --> 40:25.945
Your collection included,
amongst other things,

40:25.990 --> 40:27.082
a real shrunken head,

40:27.120 --> 40:29.953
what appeared to be
an authentic Picasso

40:29.990 --> 40:34.598
and an entire series of books
on homemade bomb building.

40:34.630 --> 40:36.222
(wry laugh)

40:36.260 --> 40:38.125
It's remarkable.

40:38.160 --> 40:41.095
You're too lazy to even
maintain a proper ruse.

40:41.130 --> 40:43.098
We're not gonna
fight, Sherlock.

40:43.140 --> 40:45.768
No matter how much
you want to.

40:50.110 --> 40:52.101
Something's wrong.

40:52.150 --> 40:54.744
You're too calm.

40:54.780 --> 40:57.613
The other night at dinner,

40:57.650 --> 40:59.618
I sought a little
advice from Joan

40:59.650 --> 41:02.118
about _how best to
communIcate WIth you.

41:02.160 --> 41:04.924
And why on earth
would you want to do that?

41:04.960 --> 41:08.726
She said that when one has
something to tell you,

41:08.760 --> 41:12.059
one must make
really, really sure

41:12.100 --> 41:14.989
that you're listening.

41:26.280 --> 41:28.714
Books on bomb building.

41:32.220 --> 41:34.859
I consider us even now.

41:37.320 --> 41:39.584
Which means I can tell you
I forgive you.

41:39.630 --> 41:41.029
For everything.

41:45.100 --> 41:48.228
Have a safe trip
back to the colonies.

41:48.270 --> 41:51.603
And know that things are
different between us now.

41:51.640 --> 41:54.063
*

42:04.280 --> 42:07.841
Hey, I was just
about to call you.

